{"type":"message","id":"78e62122","parentId":"ffd5fb44","timestamp":"2026-03-27T21:05:04.682Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the sessions_list results:\n\n1. The first session is the cron job session itself (agent:main:cron:3709e1d2-67b1-4eff-92e4-b586ec802978) - this is this very cron job run, not a user conversation.\n\n2. The second session is another cron job (Cron: 服务状态巡检) - also not a user conversation.\n\nNeither of these are active user conversations. The last user message would be from the user's actual conversation","thinkingSignature":""}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1141,"output":0,"cacheRead":43981,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45122,"cost":{"input":0.00034229999999999997,"output":0,"cacheRead":0.00131943,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00166173}},"stopReason":"error","timestamp":1774645434628,"errorMessage":"terminated"}}
{"type":"message","id":"edf868cf","parentId":"78e62122","timestamp":"2026-03-27T21:05:15.483Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the sessions list, I can see two cron sessions:\n1. \"Cron: 空闲检测自主学习\" - this is the current cron job itself, with a message from the assistant about checking sessions\n2. \"Cron: 服务状态巡检\" - another cron job\n\nThe question is whether there are any **user** conversations active in the last 5 minutes. The sessions shown are both cron jobs (system-initiated), not user conversations. But let me check if there's a \"main\" session with recent user activity.\n\nLooking at the sessions:\n- Both sessions are cron jobs (kind: \"other\"), not user conversations\n- There's no agent:main:user or agent:main:feishu session with recent activity\n\nHowever, I should be more careful. The sessions_list with activeMinutes=5 should only show sessions updated in the last 5 minutes. Both sessions show recent update times, but they're both cron sessions, not user conversations.\n\n\nThe cron job session from 17:03 has context tokens indicating it processed content, but that's just the job itself responding to the cron trigger. I need to check for actual user sessions like agent:main or those with the feishu channel to find real user activity.","thinkingSignature":"70c1c1298a22407b1a38c7beaa0c809ff248d00f8452968bed4a1310273b5954"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_h0roz0nzyoe8_1","name":"sessions_list","arguments":{"activeMinutes":5,"messageLimit":1}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_h0roz0nzyoe8_2","name":"sessions_list","arguments":{"limit":10,"messageLimit":1}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1141,"output":318,"cacheRead":43981,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45440,"cost":{"input":0.00034229999999999997,"output":0.0003816,"cacheRead":0.00131943,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00204333}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774645506749}}
